HEADWORD: Litigation
<hw>Lit`i*ga"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>litigatio</ets>, fr. <ets>litigare</ets> to dispute, litigate;
<ets>lis</ets>, <ets>litis</ets>, dispute, lawsuit (OL.
<ets>stlis</ets>) + <ets>agere</ets> to carry on. See
<er>Agent</er>.]</ety> <def>The act or process of litigating; a suit at
law; a judicial contest.</def>⟦br⟧
